[![Open in Gitpod](https://gitpod.io/button/open-in-gitpod.svg)](https://gitpod.io/from-referrer/)

Almost last part of porting project of the [formalization of polynomial ABC](https://github.com/seewoo5/lean-poly-abc).
This file proves Mason-Stothers theorem (i.e. polynomial ABC). For coprime polynomials $a, b, c$ over a field (of arbitrary characteristic) with $a + b + c = 0$, we have $\max\{\deg(a), \deg(b), \deg(c)\} + 1 \le \deg(\mathrm{rad}(abc))$ or $a' = b' = c' = 0$.

TODO: After #14720 is merged, add polynomial FLT as a corollary. It is already in [here](https://github.com/seewoo5/lean-poly-abc/blob/main/LeanPolyABC/Corollaries/FltCatalan.lean).
